
crypt(char *plaintext, char *salt); returns a char *ciphertext (in
  human readable form) (man 3 crypt)

Tools for cryptography:
-----------------------
 1. random number generator
 2. hashing function
      arbitrary data --[SHA-256]--> 256-bit hash
        (a) two different strings do not hash to same value
        (b) "impossible" to reverse the function
        (c) fast
 3. block cipher (shared key) AES
 4. key exchange algorithm
